  "12-11": (
    caption: [Calmodulin. This is the protein mediator of many Ca2(cid:3)- stimulated enzymatic reactions. Calmodulin has four high-affinity Ca2(cid:3)- binding sites (Kd (cid:2) 0.1 to 1 (cid:5)M). (a) A ribbon model of the crystal struc- ture of calmodulin (PDB ID 1CLL). The four Ca2(cid:3)-binding sites are occupied by Ca2(cid:3) (purple). The amino-terminal domain is on the left; the carboxyl-terminal domain on the right. (b) Calmodulin associated with a helical domain (red) of one of the many enzymes it regulates, calmodulin-dependent protein kinase II (PDB ID 1CDL). Notice that the long central (cid:3) helix of calmodulin visible in (a) has bent back on itself in binding to the helical substrate domain. The central helix of calmodulin is clearly more flexible in solution than in the crystal. (c) Each of the four Ca2(cid:3)-binding sites occurs in a helix-loop-helix motif called the EF hand, also found in many other Ca2(cid:3)-binding proteins.],
