  "12-25": (
    caption: [Transmembrane electrical potential. (a) The electrogenic Na(cid:3)K(cid:3) ATPase produces a transmembrane electrical potential of about (cid:2)60 mV (inside negative). (b) Blue arrows show the direction in which ions tend to move spontaneously across the plasma membrane in an animal cell, driven by the combination of chemical and electrical gradi- ents. The chemical gradient drives Na(cid:3) and Ca2(cid:3) inward (producing depolarization) and K(cid:3) outward (producing hyperpolarization). The electrical gradient drives Cl(cid:2) outward, against its concentration gradient (producing depolarization).],
