    caption: [The acetylcholine receptor ion channel. (a) Each of the five homologous subunits ((cid:2)2(cid:3)(cid:4)(cid:5)) has four transmembrane helices, M1 to M4. The M2 helices are amphipathic; the others have mainly hydro- phobic residues. (b) The five subunits are arranged around a central transmembrane channel, which is lined with the polar sides of the M2 helices. At the top and bottom of the channel are rings of negatively charged amino acid residues. (c) A molecular model of the acetylcholine receptor, based on x-ray structure determination of a related protein (the acetylcholine-binding protein from a mollusk; PDB ID 1UV6). (d) This cartoon view of a cross section through the center of the M2 helices],
