  "12-29": (
    caption: [Two-way signaling by integrins. All integrins have one (cid:3) and one (cid:2) subunit, each with a short cytoplasmic extension, a single transmembrane helix, and a large extracellular domain with the ligand- binding site. The (cid:2) subunit (purple) is rich in Cys residues and has exten- sive intrachain disulfide bonding. The (cid:3) subunit (pink) in many integrins has several binding sites for divalent cations such as Ca2(cid:3), which are intrinsic to the ligand-binding activity. In its inactive state, integrin’s extra- cellular domain is folded upon itself (center). Contact with an extracellular ligand (collagen or heparan sulfate, for example) straightens the extracel-],
