  "12-43": (
    caption: [Common features of signaling systems that detect hor- mones, light, smells, and tastes. GPCRs provide signal specificity, and their interaction with G proteins provides signal amplification. Heterotri- meric G proteins activate effector enzymes: adenylyl cyclase (AC), phospholipase C (PLC), and phosphodiesterases (PDEs) that degrade cAMP or cGMP. Changes in concentration of the second messengers (cAMP, cGMP, IP3) result in alterations of enzymatic activities by phos- phorylation or alterations in the permeability (P) of surface membranes],
